candatchk: A mid level corporate finance position (e.g., controller, treasury staff, investor relations staff)
opencncrn: I don't have any. I trust the test and they've been working for 4 years. Seems like they would be a good candidate. Maybe I would be concerned that they didn't get promoted in that time.
openresolv: Ask them about their work style. Ask them to tell me about a time they made a mistake and what they learned from it. If I was really concerned, I would ask them directly why they stayed in the same position the whole time.
oe_qual: They were able to complete their degree in 4 years, so I assume they can manage their time and probably come from a family of other white collar workers, so they will share cultural knowledge and habits with me and the rest of the staff. They worked at the same place for 4 years, which says to me they must've been sufficiently competent not to get fired.
oe_comm: They worked at the same place for 4 years. That's a pretty long run for a worker today. Either they were committed to their former workplace or they don't really care to look for better work.
oe_interview: I don't see any red flags and I'm generally optimistic that anyone with sufficient training could do these financial jobs. You don't really need any special characteristics, just training.
oe_offer: We need a worker and this person will fill the job.
oe_referral: They stayed in their previous position for 4 years and they completed their degree in just 4 years. They seems to be a person to stays the path and wouldn't make any risky or sudden changes.
